<p>Follow this steps:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Connect the shorter leg of the LED to GPIO 5 (pin 29 on the expansion header).</li>
  <li>Connect the longer leg of the LED to the resistor.</li>
  <li>Connect the other end of the resistor to one of the 3.3V pins on the board.</li>
  <li>Note that the polarity of the LED is important. (This configuration is commonly known as Active Low)</li>
</ol>
